properties.headline: Small Craft Advisory issued January 18 at 3:34PM CST until January 20 at 12:00PM CST by NWS Mobile AL
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the Small Craft Advisory through this afternoon, seas
5 to 7 feet. For the Small Craft Advisory late tonight through
Monday, north winds increasing to 15 to 25 knots with gusts up
to 30 knots. Seas 5 to 8 feet expected, especially well
offshore.

* WHERE...Coastal waters from Pensacola FL to Pascagoula MS out
20 NM, Coastal waters from Okaloosa Walton County Line FL to
Pensacola FL out 20 NM, Waters from Pensacola FL to Pascagoula
MS from 20 to 60 NM and Waters from Okaloosa Walton County
Line FL to Pensacola FL from 20 to 60 NM.

* WHEN...Small Craft Advisory for seas 5 to 7 feet until 6 PM CST
this evening. Another Small Craft Advisory goes into effect from
3 AM Sunday to noon CST Monday for the increased northerly winds
and seas.

* IMPACTS...Conditions will be hazardous to small craft.
properties.instruction:
Inexperienced mariners, especially those operating smaller
vessels, should avoid navigating in hazardous conditions.

NWSheadline: SMALL CRAFT ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 PM CST THIS EVENING... ...SMALL CRAFT ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 3 AM SUNDAY TO NOON CST MONDAY
